Business Brief -- Sundstrand Corp.:
   Aerospace Division to Lose
   155 Workers; Market Cited
Sundstrand said the cuts will be made in Rockford, where
there are about 3,550 workers. The company has 12,500
employees world-wide.
   The company said it is "well-positioned" to take advantage
of any future growth in the economy or the aerospace
business.
   Last year, the company announced several rounds of layoffs
"to adjust its costs and employment levels to be in line with
the business outlook."